ure's Touch and Chloroblast memorized.<br><br>I have several sets of hot keys set up, too.  #1 is my solo/travel set of hot keys, #10 (immediately to the left of #1) is my group/raid set of hot keys.  #2 is my set of non-combat clicky items (e.g., Woven Grass Chestguard, Greaves, and Boots), #3 are my pet command keys, and so on. <p><b>Tresjoli Louveteau<b><br><i>Femme d'esprit</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utresjoli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tresjoli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadow-striders.com/images/wolfIcon.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/4/02 1:15:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ullyath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/7/02 8:17:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> I have spells I use on pages 1 through 10; gates on 11 through 19; then the rest, sorted. I use /book macros to get around <p><font size="-2"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15432">Llyath</a> the Preserver<br><b>Hierophant of <a href="http://www.remedy.fr.st">Remedy</a></b><br><br><i>"Beware the engineers of society, I say, who would make everyone in the world equal.<br>Opportunity should be equal, must be equal, but achievement must remain individual."<br>- From 'Streams of Silver' by R.A. Salvatore</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaegyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aegyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/17/02 12:38:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> i have 2 /book hotkeys.......NOOBS for the buffs you can't cast on lower lvl and LEETS, after that i pretty much just throw all my spells in the book and hope the right ones come out on top.<br><br>Aeg <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72782>MyStuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/17/02 10:14:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> pages 1&amp;2 get the spells I normally have memmed all the time, and while soloing<br><br>Pages 3&amp;4 get buffs, both self and shared single-target<br><br>Pages 5&amp;6 get grouping spells (grp buffs, buffs only used while grouping, debuffs, etc)<br><br>Page 7 gets resist buffs (all 5)<br><br>Page 8 gets other misc buff/util spells (bind, EB, etc)<br><br>Pages 9&amp;10 get other damage spells less frequently used (PBAoEs, other DoTs that are rarely used, rains, stuns, etc)<br><br>Pages 11 has animal charm/fear/buff/etc spells<br><br>Pages 12-13 have the other wierd, misc spells, that are not used much and don't fit any of the above categories.<br><br>Page 14 Intentionally left blank =)<br><br>Pages 15-17 have rings, 18-20 have circles, set up so:<br>the 5 least used destinations are on 17&amp;18, rings on left, circles on right.  The 10 more common destinations are rings on 15&amp;16, circles on 19&amp;20, in the same order, so for instance, ring of combines is lower right on 16, circle of combines is lower right on 20.<br><br>Page 21 is old world evacs<br><br>Page 22 is Kunark evacs, and succor<br><br>Pages 23-34 are empty<br><br>Pages 35-48 are filled with the spells I'll never cast again, just jumbled together.<br><br>Pages 49-50 are lowbie spells (SLN, Storm Strength, 49 DS, resist fire and cold, etc.)  This includes SoW, since I have the Velious quest boots.  The only time I ever have to mem SoW is on a CR =)<br><br>As far as spell slots, I haven't changed them much in ages:<br><br>1: Ensnare (always)<br>2: 56 root (always)<br>3: Best DoT (always soloing, varies grouping)<br>4: Other dmg soloing, varies grouping<br>5: Other damage or pull spell soloing, varies grouping<br>6: Imp Sup Camo or swappable buff slot soloing, swappable buff grouping<br>7: Gate/Egress/Succor/swappable TP soloing, Succor or swappable buff grouping<br>8: Chloroblast (always)<br><br>Tat<br> <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 58th Druid<BR>Ethereal, 7th Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/17/02 10:26:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> Wish this stuff were easy to unlearn.  I sometimes stop and thinkg about how I organized my spell gems over the years and now I am so used to it I can't &quot;fix&quot; it.  Same for spell book.  I do some reasonable stuff (self buffs pages 1-2, group 3-4 etc), but my original organizing principle was &quot;like spell gems go together&quot;, so all the fire spells are together (and near the cold ones).  I like the idea of the &quot;regularly used nukes&quot; all on one page but after having this setup for about 2 years (a little more) I can't imagine I can undo it.<br><br>I like that hotkey idea.  Never thought to do that and will...I have most key pages memorized (fire spells on page 26 ... don't ask me why I don't know myself)...but it would be faster if I could just hit a button.<br><br>On gems, I have always done:<br><br>1) Rotating slot for buffs<br>2) Patch heal (chloroblast -always)<br>3) Snare<br>4) Root (if on a raid, Disjunction goes here)<br>5-7) Rotates depending on need - <br>   If I am in a group, 7 is my succor slot.  That used to be 8, but now 8 I use for NT.  If in a group on a raid, 7 is for NR.  5-6 always rotate, mostly a dot and a dd (WD etc).<br>8)  If playing a cleric (helper cleric on raid or in an exp group in certain zones), this is my NT slot.  If soloing, it is my gate slot.<br><br>Heh no, I am not advocating this.  When I first got used to my keys there was no such thing as having 3 heals taht you might use at once (was in the days before Chloroblast and NT existed after all), so 1 slot for a heal made sense, etc.  Ah well, we all have our quirky ways I suppose.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A> at: 4/17/02 10:28:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf Elemental</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/17/02 3:06:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> After 60 levels of flipping through my spellbook and typing out /book X commands on the command line, I hotkeyed the first 20 pages of my spellbook.<br><br>Bank 5 now looks like this:<br>book1  book3<br>book5  book7<br>...<br>book17 book19<br><br>I only wish I'd done this sooner.  It took less time than medding to full after a quad, and has saved me a lot of time (and typing) since then.  Diving into the spellbook with &quot;Shift-5, X&quot; is very convienient.  <br><br>-Quelm, Hierophant<br>Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udasanw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dasan W</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/18/02 6:13:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dasan.8m.com/sword.gif width=50 height=50></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> When I started I copied my from a link I think was from EQDruids.. and thank god I had an outline or it would be FUBAR now :D.  <br><br>A druid book as to be the eaisest things to mess up in the whole game!  I have mine as page 1-4 general buffs (SoE, SoW, SLN, etc..), page 5-8 Damage (DD's, Dots, Debuffs), pages 9-11 resists/cures, pages 12-18 ports/succors, pages 19-20 charm/pet buffs, pages 21-50 old spells.  I had my borhter in law who plays a 52 Paly play my druid once and he vowed NEVER to play one again due to all of the spells.  He said that it was the most confusing thing he had ever seen, and yet I think I have it the most organized ever.   <p><center><EMBED src="http://dasan.8m.com/signew.swf" quality=high bgcolor=#000000 WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=85 TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/in