gured out where else to put them yet.  Etc, etc.  Pages 30-40 are the "I wish I could remove these spells from my book" area. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126501">Abru</a>, Elder Hierophant on The Nameless,  <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/index.shtml" target=_top>Legacy of Steel</a>, <a href="mailto:AbruEQ@hotmail.com">AbruEQ@hotmail.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/02 9:09:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> I used the example EQ Druids used to have on their site.  I dunno if its still there.  It worked for me until we started getting new spells, like all those damned Protection of Paper,Rock, Scissors spells.<br><br>Now after page 25 or so my book is pretty screwed heh. <p><p><center><img src=http://lilyanaeq.homestead.com/files/Signatures/Aidon.jpg><BR> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24579">Aidon</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubriennamonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BriennaMonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/02 6:02:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell book set up</span><hr size=1> I had mine set up just like the one at EQDruids, but a bunch of new spells came out in the last year and that layout didn't have &quot;holes&quot; for them :(<br><br>So, I'm attempting to come up with a better solution.<br><br>What I did with my enchanter is copy the spell list from EQCasters into a spreadsheet, then assign each spell a class (Buff, Nuke, Charm, etc).  Tried to keep the number of spells in each class under 10 (so I have &quot;melee buffs&quot;, &quot;caster buffs&quot; etc).  Then I sorted the spreadsheet into order by level and class.  Laid out the spell book in that manner and made 3 banks of hotkeys containing a hotkey for each class of spell.<br><br>Been meaning to do the same with all my casting characters but it's a lot of work to get them rearranged ingame.  Wish I could just import my spreadsheet :)<br> <p><center><font size=-2><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52964">Brienna Starrfyre</a>, level 55 human monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55569">Khieran Shadowbane</a>, level 55 human druid<br>Legacy of Darkness - Cazic Thule</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessageRange?topicID=2747.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showPrevMessage?topicID=2747.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showNextMessage?topicID=2747.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2747.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/